nib.text:
Forty-four people were displaced after a three-alarm fire in Near North late Thursday evening, officials said.

At approximately 11:03 p.m., firefighters responded to a report of a fire in the 1414 block of Plymouth Avenue North.

Upon arrival, first responders discovered a fire sweeping through the third story of an apartment building.

Citizen user video showed the flames engulfing the balcony of a third-floor apartment and spreading towards the roof.

[KSTP reported](https://kstp.com/minnesota-news/two-rescued-from-3-alarm-apartment-fire-in-north-minneapolis-by-minneapolis-fire-department/6165704/) that firefighters rescued two people from balconies.

After three alarms were called, firefighters extinguished the blaze an hour after their arrival.

The [MFD tweeted](https://twitter.com/MinneapolisFire/status/1413375630243160072) that at least forty-four people were displaced in the fire, and twenty-two apartment units are no longer livable.

The Red Cross is assisting residents in the aftermath, the MFD reported.

No injuries are reported.

The cause of the fire is still under investigation.
